data.content:
Here are the three breaking changes and fixes:

### 1. `Buffer.cs` — `[InlineArray]` on `record struct` is now an error
C# 13 disallows `[InlineArray]` on `record struct` because the compiler-generated `Equals`/`GetHashCode` only consider the first element. Change to a plain `struct`:

```csharp
[System.Runtime.CompilerServices.InlineArray(10)]
struct Buffer
{
    private int _element0;
}
```

### 2. `Generator.cs` — `stackalloc` in local function inside iterator
C# 13 relaxed `unsafe` in iterators broadly, but as a side effect, `stackalloc` in local functions within iterators is now also banned (previously they were exempt). Extract it to a separate method:

```csharp
unsafe class DataGenerator
{
    IEnumerable<int> Generate()
    {
        yield return 1;
        Process();
    }

    static void Process()
    {
        int* p = stackalloc int[10];
        // ... work with pointer
    }
}
```

### 3. `Resolver.cs` — Ambiguous overload due to new span conversions
C# 13 adds implicit conversions between `Span<T>`, `ReadOnlySpan<T>`, and arrays. This makes `Process([])` ambiguous where it previously wasn't. Fix with an explicit target type:

```csharp
Process((ReadOnlySpan<int>)[]);
```
